  id: Clavicular_intersection.R
  partName: Clavicular intersection Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right clavicular intersection is an anatomical shoulder region associated
    with remnants of the canine clavicle and surrounding muscular attachments. In
    dogs, the clavicle is greatly reduced, yet the area remains functionally important
    for forelimb mechanics and stabilization. This region supports coordinated interaction
    between the scapula, muscles, and connective tissues responsible for shoulder
    movement.
  - It contributes to maintaining proper limb positioning and flexibility during
    walking, running, and jumping activities. The clavicular intersection also assists
    with distributing mechanical forces across the shoulder complex. Injury or dysfunction
    affecting this area can compromise shoulder stability, reduce range of motion,
    and negatively influence efficient forelimb locomotion and balance.
